20buyer's%20broker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20he%20had%20to%20pay%20certain%20fees%20out%20of%20pocket%2C%20like%20the%20%24500-a-month%20listing%20fee%20on%20StreetEasy%2C%20a%20Zillow-owned%20listings%20website%20for%20New%20York%20City%20properties%20for%20sale%20or%20rent.%20But%20Chou%20told%20Insider%20he%20doesn't%20regret%20selling%20his%20apartment%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%26quot%3B%20Chou%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20seller's%20market%2C%20and%20because%20of%20that%20I%20felt%20well-equipped%20to%20be%20able%20to%20do%20so%20myself%20and%20wound%20up%20saving%20anywhere%20between%20%2430%2C000%20and%20%2450%2C000%20in%20commission.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGrunt%20work%20and%20mishaps%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Chou's%20home%20sale%20was%20successful%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20a%20lot%20of%20grunt%20work%20to%20do%20it%20consistently%20on%20a%20weekly%20basis%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20such%20as%20answering%20emails%20with%20tons%20of%20questions.%20It's%20more%20time-consuming%20than%20he%20expected%2C%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20found%20himself%20besieged%20by%20relentless%20real-estate%20agents.%20They%20had%20seen%20his%20for%20sale%20by%20owner%2C%20or%20FSBO%2C%20listing%2C%20and%20each%20broker%20was%20trying%20to%20pressure%20him%20to%20enlist%20their%20services.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20decide%20to%20sell%20on%20your%20own%2C%20be%20prepared%20to%20hear%20nonstop%20pitches%2C%26quot%3B%20Chou%20wrote%20in%20a%20post%20published%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2F%40treez217%2Fi-sold-my-manhattan-nyc-condo-for-sale-by-owner-fsbo-by-myself-and-it-almost-killed-someone-3de674656343%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EMedium%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20March%202018.%20After%20going%20through%20all%20of%20his%20emails%2C%20Chou%20realized%20he%20was%20contacted%20by%20a%20%26quot%3Btotal%20of%20110%20brokers%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20faced%20a%20setback%20when%20a%20cleaning%20mishap%20forced%20him%20to%20pull%20his%20listing%20from%20the%20market.%20In%20an%20attempt%20to%20showcase%20his%20condo's%20views%2C%20he%20hired%20window%20cleaners.%20When%20a%20window%20accidentally%20broke%20during%20the%20process%2C%20plummeting%2020%20stories%20to%20the%20streets%20of%20New%20York%2C%20Chou%20was%20forced%20to%20briefly%20take%20the%20home%20off%20the%20market%20as%20he%20endured%20a%20five-month%20wait%20for%20its%20replacement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20was%20morally%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20Chou%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20if%20you%20can%20sell%20an%20apartment%20that%20doesn't%20have%20a%20window.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20window%20was%20being%20replaced%2C%20Chou%20and%20his%20family%20temporarily%20vacated%20the%20home.%20Over%20the%20next%20few%20months%2C%20they%20found%20themselves%20shouldering%20the%20expenses%20for%20two%20New%20York%20City%20apartments%2C%20a%20costly%20situation%20that%20almost%20pushed%20him%20to%20consider%20using%20a%20broker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRight%20after%20the%20window%20incident%20happened%2C%20it%20crossed%20my%20mind%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20Chou%20persisted.%20Seven%20months%20after%20the%20window%20incident%2C%20he%20put%20the%20home%20back%20on%20the%20market.%20It%20sold%20within%20the%20year%20to%20a%20buyer%20who%20also%20did%20not%20use%20a%20broker%20%E2%80%94%20a%20rarity%20in%20New%20York's%20competitive%20and%20inventory-starved%20real-estate%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20figured%20it%20was%20going%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20Chou%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3BIt%20takes%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20and%20hard%20work%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20necessarily%20too%20complex.%20It's%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20doing%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20years%20later%2C%20with%20two%20kids%2C%20Chou%20said%20he%20would%20work%20with%20an%20agent%20if%20he%20were%20to%20sell%20again.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20know%20if%20I%20have%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20noting%20the%20kids'%20packed%20schedules%20and%20other%20family%20obligations%20he%20has%20to%20attend%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChou%20has%20turned%20his%20acquired%20real-estate%20knowledge%20into%20a%20business%20venture.%20He%20is%20now%20the%20founder%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.transparentcity.co%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETransparent%20City%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20apartment%20listing%20website%20that%20provides%20renters%20information%20on%20every%20no-fee%20management%20company%20in%20New%20York.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffor-sale-by-owner-nyc-real-estate-fee-broker-commission-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699789981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654e4df8b788914e5553e7aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffor-sale-by-owner-nyc-real-estate-fee-broker-commission-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Derrick%20Chou%20did%20the%20%26quot%3Bgrunt%20work%26quot%3B%20of%20listing%20his%20property%2C%20responding%20to%20emails%20and%20swatting%20off%20over%20100%20real-estate%20agents.%20He%20has%20no%20regrets.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22alloyd%40insider.com%20(Alcynna%20Lloyd)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffor-sale-by-owner-nyc-real-estate-fee-broker-commission-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22More%20Than%20One%20Journalist%20Per%20Day%20Is%20Dying%20in%20the%20Israel-Gaza%20Conflict.%20This%20Has%20to%26nbsp%3BStop%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F12171955%2F3078621952_12eaf824ef_c.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Committee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists%2C%20the%20Gaza-Israel%20war%20has%20been%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%5C%22%3Edeadliest%20conflict%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20media%20workers%20since%20the%20organisation%20began%20counting%20statistics%20in%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20writing%2C%20the%20committee%20said%20at%20least%2039%20journalists%20and%20media%20workers%20had%20been%20killed%20in%20the%20month%20since%20the%20war%20began.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frsf.org%2Fen%2Fisraelpalestine-war-41-journalists-more-one-day-killed-first-month-israel-palestine-war%5C%22%3EReporters%20Without%20Borders%3C%2Fa%3E%20put%20the%20number%20slightly%20higher%20at%2041.%20But%20the%20rate%20of%20fatalities%20is%20so%20high%20%E2%80%93%20more%20than%20one%20per%20day%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20likely%20there%20will%20be%20more%20dead%20by%20the%20time%20you%20read%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20victims%20are%20mostly%20Palestinian%20journalists%20and%20media%20workers%20killed%20in%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20attacks%20on%20Gaza%2C%20but%20they%20include%20four%20Israelis%2C%20whom%20Hamas%20murdered%20in%20its%20initial%20cross-border%20raid%20on%20October%207%2C%20and%20one%20Beirut-based%20videographer%20killed%20in%20south%20Lebanon.%20He%20died%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Freuters-videographer-killed-southern-lebanon-2023-10-13%2F%5C%22%3Ein%20shelling%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20also%20injured%20six%20other%20journalists.%20Witnesses%20said%20the%20shelling%20came%20from%20the%20direction%20of%20Israel%20and%20hit%20a%20group%20of%20journalists%20in%20clearly%20marked%20vehicles%20and%20body%20armour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20worth%20pausing%20for%20a%20moment%20to%20remember%20these%20are%20not%20merely%20numbers.%20Each%20of%20the%20victims%20has%20a%20name%2C%20relatives%2C%20loved%20ones%20and%20a%20story.%20The%20committee%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%2F2023%2F11%2Fjournalist-casualties-in-the-israel-gaza-conflict%2F%5C%22%3Egrim%20list%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20all%20those%20who%20have%20been%20killed%2C%20injured%20or%20are%20missing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dead%20include%20Palestinian%20freelance%20journalists%20working%20for%20international%20news%20services%2C%20and%20others%20who%20work%20for%20local%20news%20outlets%20crucial%20for%20local%20understanding%20of%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening.%20Many%20have%20died%20in%20air%20strikes%20on%20their%20homes%2C%20some%20alongside%20their%20children%20and%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Israeli%20Defence%20Forces%20insist%20they%20do%20not%20target%20journalists%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frsf.org%2Fen%2Fisraelpalestine-war-41-journalists-more-one-day-killed-first-month-israel-palestine-war%5C%22%3EReporters%20Without%20Borders%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20at%20least%20ten%20have%20been%20killed%20while%20clearly%20covering%20the%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20life%20of%20a%20journalist%20is%20worth%20no%20more%20than%20any%20other%20civilian%2C%20and%20in%20such%20a%20horrifically%20violent%20crisis%2C%20which%20has%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fpressure-israel-over-civilians-steps-up-ceasefire-calls-rebuffed-2023-11-06%2F%5C%22%3Ekilled%20more%20than%2010%2C000%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20it%20is%20hardly%20surprising%20some%20of%20them%20will%20be%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20is%20mounting%20evidence%20journalists%20have%20been%20targeted%2C%20harassed%2C%20beaten%20and%20threatened.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcpj.org%2F2023%2F11%2Fattacks-arrests-threats-censorship-the-high-risks-of-reporting-the-israel-hamas-war%2F%5C%22%3ECommittee%20to%20Protect%20Journalists%20list%3C%2Fa%3E%20blames%20Israeli%20authorities%20for%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20incidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2012%2C%20Israeli%20police%20assaulted%20a%20group%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-67102956%5C%22%3EBBC%20journalists%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Tel%20Aviv%20and%20held%20them%20at%20gunpoint.%20The%20BBC%20said%20reporters%20Muhannad%20Tutunji%2C%20Haitham%20Abudiab%20and%20their%20BBC%20Arabic%20team%20were%20driving%20a%20vehicle%20clearly%20marked%20%E2%80%9CTV%E2%80%9D%20in%20red%20tape%2C%20and%20both%20Tutunji%20and%20Abudaib%20presented%20their%20press%20cards.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20October%2016%2C%20Israeli%20journalist%20and%20columnist%20Israel%20Frey%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DzMKyH4jCnTE%5C%22%3Ewent%20into%20hiding%3C%2Fa%3E%20after%20a%20mob%20of%20far-right%20Israelis%20attacked%20his%20home%20the%20previous%20day.%20The%20mob%20was%20apparently%20angry%20at%20a%20column%20he%20wrote%20expressing%20sympathy%20for%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%205%2C%20Israeli%20police%20arrested%2030-year-old%20freelance%20Palestinian%20journalist%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.madacenter.org%2Fen%2Farticle%2F1449%2F%5C%22%3ESomaya%20Jawabra%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Nablus%20in%20the%20northern%20West%20Bank.%20She%20was%20summoned%2C%20along%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20journalist%20Tariq%20Al-Sarkaji%2C%20for%20an%20investigation.%20Her%20husband%20was%20later%20released%20but%20Jawabra%2C%20who%20is%20seven%20months%20pregnant%2C%20remains%20in%20detention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifj.org%2Fmedia-centre%2Fnews%2Fdetail%2Fcategory%2Fpress-releases%2Farticle%2Fglobal-call-israel-must-commit-to-protecting-journalists%5C%22%3EInternational%20Federation%20of%20Journalists%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20called%20on%20the%20Israeli%20government%20to%20rigorously%20observe%20international%20law%20that%20requires%20combatants%20to%20take%20all%20reasonable%20steps%20to%20treat%20journalists%20as%20civilians%20and%20safeguard%20their%20lives.%20The%20Israeli%20military%20has%20told%20at%20least%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fisraeli-military-says-it-cant-guarantee-journalists-safety-gaza-2023-10-27%2F%5C%22%3Etwo%20international%20news%20agencies%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20cannot%20guarantee%20the%20safety%20of%20their%20staff%20covering%20the%20Gaza%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPropaganda%20war%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20matters%2C%20and%20not%20just%20to%20the%20reporters%20who%20are%20putting%20their%20lives%20on%20the%20line%20or%20being%20attacked%20and%20abused.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20digitally%20connected%20world%2C%20distortions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fisrael-hamas-gaza-misinformation-fact-check-e58f9ab8696309305c3ea2bfb269258e%5C%22%3Edisinformation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20outright%20lies%20speed%20around%20the%20world%20faster%20than%20a%20ballistic%20missile.%20The%20online%20narrative%20is%20at%20least%20as%20important%20as%20the%20fighting%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20as%20each%20side%20works%20to%20portray%20itself%20as%20the%20victim%2C%20harnessing%20numbers%20and%20narratives%20to%20support%20their%20arguments%20and%20win%20backing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20real%20consequences.%20In%20the%20propaganda%20war%2C%20public%20support%20translates%20to%20political%2C%20financial%20and%20even%20military%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20appears%20to%20be%20one%20reason%20why%20Israel%20has%20repeatedly%20imposed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F11%2F1%2Fisrael-imposes-communication-blackout-on-gaza-second-time-in-five-days%5C%22%3Ecommunications%20blackouts%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Gaza.%20As%20the%20crisis%20draws%20on%2C%20painful%20stories%20about%20the%20consequences%20of%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20attacks%20erode%20public%20support%3B%20controlling%20the%20narrative%20becomes%20increasingly%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20journalists%20are%20killed%20or%20intimidated%20away%20from%20their%20work%2C%20the%20more%20space%20there%20is%20for%20the%20propagandists%20of%20both%20sides%20to%20work%20unhindered.%20Without%20good%20journalists%2C%20we%20are%20forced%20to%20rely%20on%20unchecked%20and%20unchallenged%20statements%20from%20protagonists%2C%20or%20unfiltered%20social%20media%20posts%20that%20create%20more%20confusion%20than%20clarity.%20Neither%20gives%20us%20a%20solid%20basis%20for%20understanding%20what%20is%20really%20going%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20why%20good%20journalism%20is%20more%20important%20than%20ever.%20Journalists%20are%20not%20perfect%2C%20of%20course%2C%20but%20most%20trade%20on%20their%20credibility.%20They%20rely%20on%20well-established%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifj.org%2Fwho%2Frules-and-policy%2Fglobal-charter-of-ethics-for-journalists%5C%22%3Eprofessional%20protocols%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20commit%20them%20to%20factual%20accuracy%2C%20independence%2C%20rights-of-reply%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20they%20give%20their%20work%20a%20degree%20of%20trust%20that%20keeps%20their%20readers%20and%20audiences%20coming%20back%20for%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECollectively%2C%20the%20goal%20is%20to%20create%20a%20core%20of%20information%20that%20is%20reliably%20independent%20and%20%E2%80%93%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20in%20a%20crisis%20as%20foggy%20as%20this%20one%20%E2%80%93%20broadly%20accurate.%20Without%20that%20commitment%2C%20journalists%20lose%20their%20authority%20and%20hence%20their%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20is%20so%20crucial%20that%20the%20United%20Nations%20has%20created%20a%20special%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unesco.org%2Fen%2Fsafety-journalists%2Fun-plan-action%3FTSPD_101_R0%3D080713870fab2000b574785dd284b33d415bcb7212995e0107d37fa39f2de85c400d7a9ae875e2aa086d8eb45714300025cd580abf3788c43674045df43bf91bb48d16fe7db539ad762bb44504efd0e165ad95941a05b1ede3b3b5347a9c949a%5C%22%3EPlan%20of%20Action%20on%20the%20Safety%20of%20Journalists%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20plan%