eeded%3B%20and%20who%20understand%20that%20their%20job%20is%20to%20make%20two%20decisions.%20The%20first%20is%20to%20replace%20the%20manager%20or%20CEO%3B%20the%20second%20is%20to%20sell%20the%20club.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwarren-buffett-berkshire-hathaway-business-ownership-structure-greg-abel-successor-2023-5%5C%22%3Espoken%20to%20several%20CEOs%20of%20Berkshire%20subsidiaries%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20and%20they've%20painted%20a%20similar%20picture%20to%20Ferguson.%20Buffett%20trusts%20them%20to%20manage%20their%20businesses%20for%20the%20long%20term%2C%20but%20he's%20just%20a%20call%20away%20if%20they%20need%20funding%20or%20advice.%20He%20and%20his%20business%20partner%2C%20Charlie%20Munger%2C%20have%20also%20replaced%20managers%20who%20weren't%20working%20out%2C%20and%20disposed%20of%20businesses%20that%20were%20burning%20cash%20and%20couldn't%20be%20fixed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBuffett%20has%20structured%20Berkshire%20as%20a%20web%20of%20decentralized%2C%20autonomous%20subsidiaries%20to%20suit%20his%20hands-off%20approach.%20He's%20described%20his%20management%20style%20as%20%26quot%3Bdelegation%20just%20short%20of%20abdication.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApple%20cofounder%20Steve%20Jobs%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dfj0hpsJvrko%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eonce%20voiced%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20similar%20philosophy.%20%26quot%3BThe%20greatest%20people%20are%20self-managing%2C%20they%20don't%20need%20to%20be%20managed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20they%20need%20is%20a%20common%20vision%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20leadership%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJobs%20added%20that%20a%20leader's%20job%20is%20to%20have%20a%20larger%20vision%2C%20articulate%20it%20others%2C%20and%20build%20consensus%20around%20realizing%20it.%20Buffett%20has%20taken%20the%20same%20approach%2C%20enshrining%20his%20core%20val