ed%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20Soledar%20in%202022.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650b6b4712dc4f001a177035%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Soledar%20building%20lies%20in%20ruin.%3Cp%3ETania%20Synia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20eastern%20Ukrainian%20city%20of%20Soledar%20fell%20to%20Russia%20in%20January%20after%20months%20of%20brutal%20battle.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ESoledar%20and%20neighboring%20Bakhmut%20were%20once%20the%20site%20of%20the%20war's%20most%20intense%20fighting.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThree%20people%20who%20were%20in%20Soledar%20at%20that%20time%20spoke%20to%20Insider%20about%20the%20carnage%20they%20witnessed.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20was%20already%20in%20ruins%20when%20Tania%20Synia%20arrived%20in%20Soledar%20in%20August%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2026-year-old%20Ukrainian%20photographer%20and%20humanitarian%20volunteer%20traveled%20to%20the%20besieged%20town%20in%20late%20summer%20last%20year%20to%20help%20evacuate%20civilians%20less%20than%20two%20weeks%20after%20Russian%20assaults%20on%20the%20small%20city%20began%20in%20earnest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20like%20a%20movie.%20There%20was%20bombing%20everywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20Synia%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20were%20dogs%20in%20the%20streets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20be%20another%20five%20months%20before%20the%20eastern%20Ukrainian%20city%2C%20located%2010%20miles%20northeast%20of%20Bakhmut%2C%20would%20fall%20to%20Russia%20as%20the%20new%20year%20dawned.%20Five%20long%20months%20of%20air%20strikes%20and%20artillery%20attacks%20ravaged%20the%20salt-mining%20town%20as%20Russia%20came%20to%20see%20the%20seizure%20of%20Soledar%20as%20a%20path%20to%20victory%20in%20the%20larger%20city%20of%20Bakhmut.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoledar%20remained%20under%20Ukrainian%20control%20until%20mid-January%2C%20when%20Yevgeny%20Prigozhin%2C%20the