3EUnder%20increasing%20pressure%20from%20new%20competition%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-model-3-model-y-less-than-average-gas-car-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETesla%20spent%20the%20past%20year%20slashing%20the%20average%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20models%20by%20roughly%2025%25.%20The%20Model%203%20fell%20from%20%2448%2C000%20to%20%2444%2C380.%20The%20luxury%20Model%20S%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20plunged%20from%20a%20high%20of%20%24130%2C000%20to%20%2496%2C380.%20The%20cars%2C%20as%20they%20say%2C%20have%20been%20priced%20to%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20unusual%20business%20strategy%2C%20to%20put%20it%20mildly.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20think%20of%20another%20point%20in%20the%20history%20of%20automotive%20when%20a%20brand%20that%20wasn't%20going%20out%20of%20business%20cut%20prices%2020%25%20a%20year%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Schirmer%2C%20the%20director%20of%20communications%20at%20the%20research%20firm%20Cox%20Automotive%2C%20told%20me.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteslas-price-cuts-margins-ever-musk-not-giving-up2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETesla%20is%20hoping%20that%20lower%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20drive%20up%20sales%20and%20slow%20the%20advance%20of%20the%20company's%20rivals%20%E2%80%94%20maybe%20even%20scare%20some%20of%20them%20out%20of%20the%20market%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that's%20not%20what's%20happening.%20Lower%20prices%20are%20not%20translating%20into%20higher%20sales.%20The%20number%20of%20cars%20Tesla%20delivered%20to%20customers%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%20actually%20declined.%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3ERevenue%20is%20dropping%2C%20and%20the%20company's%20once%20fat%20profit%20margins%20are%20getting%20squeezed%20%E2%80%94%20down%20to%2017.9%25%20in%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20compared%20with%2025.1%25%20a%20year%20ago.%20Competitors%20aren't%20being%20driven%20out%20of%20business%2C%20either.%20Once%20totally%20dominant%20in%20the%20EV%20space%2C%20Tesla's%20share%20of%20the%20US%20market%20has%20fallen%20from%2062%25%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.coxautoinc.com%2Fmarket-insights%2Fq3-2023-ev-sales%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20only%2050%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20make%20matters%20worse%2C%20the%20public's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauto-executives-coming-clean-evs-arent-working-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eappetite%20for%20EVs%20isn't%20growing%20as%20fast%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20automakers%20expected.%20That%20means%20Tesla%20has%20set%20off%20a%20protracted%20battle%20for%20a%20piece%20of%20a%20pie%20that's%20growing%20crumb%20by%20crumb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20do%20the%20price%20war%2C%20you%20have%20to%20make%20sure%20you%20have%20enough%20volume%20to%20increase%20and%20maintain%20profitability%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Zhang%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20marketing%20at%20the%20Wharton%20School%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20to%20be%20a%20continuous%20battle.%20This%20war%20you%20have%20to%20wage%20all%20the%20way.%20And%20you%20need%20to%20plan%20ahead.%20That's%20how%20you%20win.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20some%20experts%20will%20tell%20you%20that%20price%20wars%20are%20unwinnable%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0that%20they're%20a%20race%20to%20the%20bottom%20that%20serves%20only%20to%20kill%20profitability%20for%20the%20entire%20industry.%20And%20in%20an%20industry%20where%20the%20underlying%20technology%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20thus%2C%20the%20costs%20of%20production%20%E2%80%94%20are%20changing%20rapidly%2C%20no%20one%20can%20be%20sure%20where%20the%20bottom%20is.%20Winnable%20or%20not%2C%20Musk%20chose%20a%20terrible%20time%20to%20pick%20a%20fight.%20As%20legacy%20automakers%20walk%20the%20tightrope%20to%20our%20electric%20future%2C%20they%20can%20rely%20on%20sales%20of%20their%20traditional%20combustion-engine%20vehicles%20to%20provide%20them%20with%20a%20safety%20net.%20Tesla%20has%20no%20safety%20net.%20For%20Musk%2C%20it's%20go%20electric%2C%20or%20bust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETesla%20creates%20a%20cash%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20again%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20decision%20to%20offer%20deep%20discounts%20on%20his%20vehicles%20was%20an%20act%20of%20pure%20desperation.%20That%20became%20apparent%20earlier%20this%20month%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-earnings-q3-report-live-updates-guidance-analyst-call-stock-reaction-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETesla%20reported%20its%20third-quarter%20numbers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20results%20were%20frightful%20across%20the%20board%3A%20Tesla%20missed%20Wall%20Street's%20expectations%20on%20revenue%2C%20vehicle%20deliveries%2C%20and%20free%20cash%20flow%2C%20which%20was%20down%20to%20%24848%20million%20from%20%243.4%20billion%20a%20year%20before.%20Most%20importantly%2C%20the%20company%20reported%20that%20its%20gross%20margins%20%E2%80%94%20a%20measure%20of%20the%20company's%20profitability%20after%20costs%20%E2%80%94%20continued%20to%20shrink.%20This%20horrified%20investors%20who%20had%20just%20gotten%20used%20to%20Tesla%20making%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20despite%20Tesla's%20addition%20of%20more%20moderately%20priced%20vehicles%20such%20as%20the%20Model%203%20sedan%20and%20the%20Model%20Y%20compact%20SUV%2C%20its%20margins%20have%20grown%20to%20be%20some%20of%20the%20fattest%20in%20the%20car%20business.%20That%20has%20bolstered%20the%20argument%20that%20Tesla%20wasn't%20a%20traditional%20car%20company%20such%20as%20Ford%20or%20GM%20and%20deserved%20its%20much%2C%20much%20higher%20stock%20price.%20Naturally%2C%20this%20is%20a%20status%20Musk%20would%20like%20Tesla%20to%20keep%2C%20so%20he's%20promised%20to%20do%20everything%20he%20can%20to%20cut%20costs.%20(On%20the%20conference%20call%20on%20third-quarter%20earnings%2C%20he%20said%20it's%20like%20%26quot%3B'Game%20of%20Thrones%2C'%20but%20with%20pennies.%26quot%3B)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20cost%20cuts%20can't%20be%20spoken%20into%20existence%2C%20not%20even%20by%20Musk.%20In%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20Tesla's%20capital%20expenditures%20actually%20ballooned%20to%20their%20highest%20level%20in%20a%20year%20%E2%80%94%20%242.4%20billion%2C%20up%20from%20%241.8%20billion%20a%20year%20ago.%20If%20prices%20are%20going%20down%2C%20and%20costs%20are%20going%20up%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Ftesla-stock-q3-earnings-reactions-valuation-looks-increasingly-unsustainable-tsla-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeven%20the%20most%20fervent%20of%20Musk's%20Wall%20Street%20believers%3C%2Fa%3E%20will%20tell%20you%20that%20margins%20don't%20have%20a%20prayer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20gave%20no%20indication%20of%20when%20this%20cash%20drought%20would%20end%20or%20how%20margins%20would%20improve.%20He%20could%20not%20say%20when%20the%20company's%20Cybertruck%20would%20be%20available%20to%20the%20public%20and%20even%20admitted%20that%20Tesla%20had%20%26quot%3Bdug%20its%20own%20grave%26quot%3B%20trying%20to%20build%20the%20new%20vehicle.%20He%20also%20could%20not%20provide%20details%20on%20when%20there%20would%20be%20a%20meaningful%20update%20to%20the%20aging%20models%20that%20currently%20make%20up%20Tesla's%20fleet.%20But%20there%20was%20one%20thing%20Musk%20%3Cem%3Ewas%3C%2Fem%3E%20clear%20on%3A%20Prices%20need%20to%20keep%20coming%20down.%20In%20a%20call%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-earnings-mini-disaster-stock-price-wall-street-analyst-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20widely%20acknowledged%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20one%20of%20Tesla's%20worst%20in%20some%20time%2C%20it%20was%20like%20a%20mantra%20Musk%20repeated%20over%20and%20over%20again%2C%20with%20a%20certainty%20borne%20more%20of%20faith%20than%20facts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20just%20can't%20emphasize%20again%20how%20important%20cost%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20an%20optional%20thing%20for%20most%20people.%20It%20is%20a%20necessary%20thing.%20We%20have%20to%20make%20our%20cars%20more%20affordable%20so%20that%20people%20can%20buy%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20real%20hope%20Musk%20offered%20investors%20was%20a%20suggestion%20that%20driverless-car%20technology%20would%20(eventually%2C%20someday)%20offset%20Tesla's%20falling%20prices.%20But%20how%20exactly%20the%20math%20would%20work%20on%20that%20trade-off%20was%20unclear.%20Months%20into%20his%20pricing%20campaign%2C%20Musk%20has%20nothing%20to%20show%20for%20it%2C%20and%20no%20plans%20to%20change.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Felon-musk-tesla-stock-share-price-cybertruck-earnings-valuation-wipeout-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emarket%20responded%20to%20Musk's%20disappearing%20profits%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20dragging%20Tesla's%20stock%20down%2015%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20whole%20EV%20market%20is%20in%20a%20cash%20bleed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETesla's%20dismal%20results%20illuminated%20Musk's%20short-term%20reason%20for%20the%20desperate%20pricing%20strategy.%20But%20the%20underlying%20reason%20is%20even%20more%20alarming%3A%20Despite%20increasing%20demand%20and%20bountiful%20government%20investment%2C%20the%20world's%20transition%20from%20gas%20to%20electric%20cars%20is%20not%20going%20as%20smoothly%20as%20automakers%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20will%20tell%20you%20with%20certainty%20that%20EVs%20are%20the%20future%20and%20that%20internal-combustion%20engines%20will%20eventually%20disappear%20from%20America's%20driveways%20and%20parking%20lots.%20But%20the%20march%20to%20electrified%20highways%20isn't%20proceeding%20in%20a%20straight%20line.%20There%20are%20two%20main%20reasons%20that%20consumer%20appetite%20for%20EVs%20hasn't%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fautomakers-over-estimated-electric-vehicle-demand-early-adopters-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20robust%20as%20automakers%20initially%20expected%3C%2Fa%3E.%20One%20is%20the%20uneven%20way%20new%20technologies%20are%20adopted%3B%20it%20inevitably%20takes%20awhile%20to%20sell%20people%20on%20even%20the%20most%20amazing%20innovation.%20The%20other%20is%20the%20slowing%20global%20economy.%20Customers%20around%20the%20world%20have%20become%20more%20price-sensitive%2C%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectrc-vehicle-demand-problem-affordability-expense-price-cost-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebad%20news%20for%20EVs%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20While%20the%20average%20selling%20price%20of%20an%20electric%20vehicle%20is%20going%20down%20%E2%80%94%20from%20%2465%2C000%20last%20year%20to%20%2453%2C633%20in%20July%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20still%20higher%20than%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.coxautoinc.com%2Fmarket-insights%2Fkbb-atp-august-2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20average%20selling%20price%20for%20new%20vehicles%20overall%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20hovers%20around%20%2448%2C451.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%20onstage%20with%20a%20Cybertruck.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6536227796f7540cd062bcb1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222826%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhile%20other%20automakers%20like%20Ford%20and%20BMW%20can%20coast%20on%20older%20models%2C%20Tesla%20doesn't%20have%20that%20option.%3Cp%3EFrederic%20J.%20Brown%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETraditional%20carmakers%2C%20from%20Ford%20and%20GM%20to%20BMW%20and%20Mercedes%2C%20have%20responded%20to%20the%20EV%20price%20challenge%20by%20doing%20what%20they%20do%20best%3A%20building%20the%20gas%20cars%20that%20customers%20still%20want.%20%26quot%3BFord%20is%20able%20to%20balance%20production%20of%20gas%2C%20hybrid%2C%20and%20electric%20vehicles%20to%20match%20the%20speed%20of%20EV%20adoption%20in%20a%20way%20that%20others%20can't%2C%26quot%3B%20John%20Lawler%2C%20Ford's%20chief%20financial%20officer%2C%20said%20during%20the%20company's%20latest%20earnings%20call.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20obviously%20good%20for%20customers%2C%20who%20get%20the%20products%20they%20want%20%E2%80%94%20and%20good%20for%20us%2C%20too%2C%20because%20disciplined%20capital%20allocation%20and%20not%20chasing%20scale%20at%20all%20costs%20maximizes%20profitability%20and%20cash%20flow.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20while%20the%20traditional%20automakers%20can%20coast%20on%20their%20older%20models%2C%20Tesla%20doesn't%20have%20that%20option.%20Cue%20the%20price%20cuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMusk's%20starting%20a%20price%20war%2C%26quot%3B%20Schirmer%20of%20Cox%20Automotive%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20there%20was%20nothing%20else%20he%20could%20do%2C%20in%20that%20he%20doesn't%20have%20anything%20really%20new%20to%20compete%20against%20these%20other%20companies.%20He%20says%20it%20isn't%20because%20he%20has%20a%20demand%20problem.%20But%20I've%20been%20in%20this%20business%20a%20long%20time%2C%20and%20I%20have%20never%20seen%20anyone%20cut%20prices%20without%20having%20a%20demand%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20goal%20to%20undercut%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20market%20on%20price%20is%20no%20secret%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20made%20other%20car%20companies%20none%20too%20happy.%20Given%20the%20uncertainty%20around%20the%20future%20of%20EVs%2C%20almost%20every%20other%20automaker%20is%20reluctant%20to%20slash%20prices%20on%20their%20models%20because%20doing%20so%20would%20make%20continued%20investment%20in%20EV%20tech%20an%20even%20tougher%20business%20case%20to%20make.%20In%20April%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffortune.com%2F2023%2F04%2F21%2Felon-musk-tesla-price-cuts-could-start-pricing-war-ford-ceo-jim-farley%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFord%20CEO%20Jim%20Farley%20said%20Tesla's%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20start%20an%20unsustainable%20price%20war.%20But%20the%20company%20still%20felt%20forced%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fford-mustang-mach-e-price-cuts-tesla-price-war-electric-cars-evs-2023-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecut%20the%20price%20of%20its%20Mustang%20Mach-E%20SUV%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20least%20twice%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20auto%20executives%20are%20refusing%20to%20engage%20in%20Musk's%20fight%20because%20they%20know%20from%20experience%20that%20the%20best%20way%20to%20win%20a%20price%20war%20is%20not%20to%20get%20into%20one%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20no%20interest%20in%20sinking%20prices%20to%20gain%20market%20share%2C%26quot%3B%20BMW%20CEO%20Oliver%20Zipse%20said%20in%20a%20recent%20call%20with%20investors.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20our%20strategy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%2C%20more%20imaginative%2C%20more%20savvy%20ways%20to%20entice%20customers%20without%20a%20fire%20sale.%20During%20the%202008%20recession%2C%20rather%20than%20slashing%20prices%2C%20Hyundai%20tried%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20was%20holding%20customers%20back%20from%20buying%20a%20new%20car.%20Turns%20out%2C%20it%20was%20worries%20over%20getting%20laid%20off.%20So%20Hyundai%20offered%20customers%20a%20guarantee%3A%20Anyone%20who%20bought%20a%20car%20and%20then%20lost%20their%20job%20could%20sell%20it%20back%20to%20the%20company.%20That's%20the%20kind%20of%20creative%20work-around%20that%20gets%20a%20car%20company%20through%20hard%20times%20unscathed.%20It's%20an%20exercise%20in%20market%20research%20and%20advertising.%20Tesla%20has%20given%20little%20indication%20that%20it%20does%20the%20former%20and%20has%20flatly%20rejected%20doing%20the%20latter.%20Musk%20has%20always%20maintained%20that%20his%20outsize%20public%20profile%20makes%20advertising%20for%20Tesla%20a%20waste.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRationally%2C%20he%20doesn't%20have%20to%20drop%20prices%20so%20fast.%20He%20can%20only%20delay%20the%20competition%2C%26quot%3B%20Navdeep%20Sodhi%2C%20a%20managing%20director%20at%20the%20pricing%20consultancy%20Sodhi%20Pricing%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20Elon%20was%20smart%2C%20he%20would%20not%20drop%20the%20price.%20Instead%2C%20he%20should%20justify%20the%20cost%20of%20ownership.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20point%20of%20advertising%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20reason%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F10%2F14%2Fas-tesla-price-cuts-concede-billions-musk-is-pushed-to-spend-on-ads.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einvestors%20are%20pushing%20Tesla%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20start%20spending%20money%20on%20it%20%E2%80%94%20is%20to%20educate%20customers%20about%20why%20Tesla's%20vehicles%20are%20worth%20their%20higher%20price%20tags.%20According%20to%20Sodhi%2C%20Tesla%20has%20a%20compelling%20argument%20to%20make%20about%20how%20much%20money%20EVs%20can%20save%20customers%20over%20time.%20Why%20slash%20prices%20if%20you%20can%20persuade%20customers%20to%20pay%20more%3F%20Building%20a%20market%20for%20a%20product%20such%20as%20an%20electric%20vehicle%20is%20a%20marathon%2C%20not%20a%20sprint.%20Traditional%20carmakers%20expect%20to%20lose%20money%20on%20their%20EVs%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future.%20Tesla%20just%20became%20profitable%20in%202021.%20If%20it%20slides%20back%20into%20the%20red%20because%20of%20its%20price%20cuts%2C%20expect%20investors%20to%20run%20in%20another%20direction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20losing%20battle%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20short-term%20point%20of%20Tesla's%20price%20cuts%20is%20to%20maintain%20its%20market%20share%20and%20sell%20more%20cars%2C%20it's%20not%20working.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20move%20could%20damage%20Tesla%20in%20the%20long%20term.%20When%20companies%20play%20with%20price%2C%20Zhang%20said%2C%20they're%20playing%20with%20customer%20expectations.%20Once%20customers%20get%20used%20to%20paying%20%2440%2C000%20for%20a%20standard%20EV%2C%20they're%20not%20going%20to%20go%20back%20to%20%2460%2C000.%20In%20a%20price%20war%2C%20you%20may%20prompt%20a%20few%20more%20people%20to%20buy%20from%20you%20today%2C%20but%20you'll%20be%20sacrificing%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20future%20sales.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20are%20all%20the%20customers%20who%20paid%20that%20%2460%2C000%20in%20the%20past.%20Learning%20that%20they%20could%20have%20saved%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20if%20they'd%20waited%20a%20few%20months%20to%20make%20their%20purchase%20has%20a%20negative%20impact%20on%20brand%20loyalty.%20In%20China%2C%20Tesla's%20price%20cuts%20even%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Fautos-transportation%2Ftesla-owners-china-protest-against-surprise-price-cuts-they-missed-2023-01-07%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esparked%20protests%20among%20owners%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20paid%20more%20for%20their%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Musk%20isn't%20thinking%20about%20the%20future.%20He%20needs%20the%20money%20he%20hopes%20to%20make%20from%20price%20cuts%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he%20needs%20it%20%3Cem%3Enow.%3C%2Fem%3E%20Making%20cars%20is%20an%20expensive%20business%2C%20and%20if%20the%20price%20cuts%20don't%20generate%20more%20demand%2C%20Tesla's%20fortune%20could%20change%20rather%20quickly.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20a%20factory%20that%20makes%20something%20and%20you're%20not%20selling%20it%2C%20you're%20losing%20huge%20money%20in%20automotive%2C%26quot%3B%20Schirmer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20moment%20when%20you%20want%20an%20experienced%20team%20of%20automotive%20executives%20at%20the%20helm%20of%20your%20company.%20Instead%2C%20Tesla%20is%20onboarding%20a%20new%20chief%20financial%20officer.%20Zach%20Kirkhorn%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Tesla%20veteran%20of%2013%20years%20who%20presided%20over%20the%20most%20profitable%20quarters%20in%20the%20company's%20history%20%E2%80%94