eral-store-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Erat%20infestations.%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20Management%20at%20many%20stores%20don't%20employ%20enough%20staff%20or%20assign%20enough%20work%20hours%20to%20run%20the%20store%2C%20employees%20previously%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20recently%20moved%20close%20to%20this%20new%20store.%20There's%20no%20Walmart%20or%20Target%20in%20the%20town%3B%20there's%20a%20family-owned%20grocery%20store%20and%20that's%20it.%20So%20when%20the%20Dollar%20General%20store%20opened%20there%2C%20it%20got%20a%20lot%20of%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20store%20went%20up%20quickly.%20One%20day%2C%20I%20saw%20a%20piece%20of%20land%20being%20cleared%2C%20and%20it%20seemed%20like%20the%20store%20was%20up%20and%20hiring%20workers%20the%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20day%20I%20worked%20there%2C%20we%20were%20supposed%20to%20stock%20the%20shelves%20before%20the%20store%20opened.%20It%20all%20looked%20brand-new%20and%20in%20good%20shape.%20There%20were%20people%20mounting%20shelves%20and%20a%20guy%20setting%20up%20cameras%20and%20registers.%20Overall%2C%20I%20was%20impressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20noticed%20a%20problem%3A%20A%20heavy%20rain%20from%20the%20night%20before%20had%20flooded%20under%20the%20outside%20door%2C%20creating%20a%20pool%20at%20least%20an%20inch%20deep%20between%20the%20outside%20and%20indoor%20entrance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20store%20opened%2C%20I%20was%20working%20one%20night%20when%20it%20was%20raining%2C%20and%20the%20wind%20was%20blowing%20against%20the%20door%20so%20hard%20that%20it%20was%20automatically%20opening.%20After%20turning%20off%20the%20automatic%20sensor%2C%20I%20stayed%20in%20front%20to%20help%20customers%20manually%20open%20the%20door%2C%20while%20rain%20steadily%20washed%20underneath%20the%20front%20entrance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20tried%20to%20keep%20the%20entrance%20dry%20using%20a%20squeegee%20and%20large%20puppy%20pads%20to%20soak%20up%20water.%20We%20called%20the%20district%20manager%20to%20ask%20if%20we%20could%20close%20the%20store%20because%20of%20the%20flooded%20lobby.%20The%20reply%20was%3A%20%26quot%3BYou'll%20have%20to%20suck%20it%20up%20and%20do%20the%20best%20you%20can.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFortunately%2C%20no%20one%20slipped%20and%20fell%20when%20I%20was%20working%20there.%20Having%20to%20babysit%20the%20lobby%2C%20however%2C%20did%20prevent%20me%20from%20doing%20other%20work%20such%20as%20stocking%20shelves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20more%20problems%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20the%20months%20after%20we%20opened%20to%20shoppers.%20One%20set%20of%20freezers%20broke%20down%20three%20times.%20The%20repairman%20let%20loose%20expletives%2C%20because%20to%20repair%20them%2C%20all%20the%20freezers%20had%20to%20be%20taken%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20meant%20all%20the%20food%20inside%20had%20to%20be%20taken%20out%20and%20tossed%3A%20tater%20tots%2C%20pizzas%2C%20and%20frozen%20meals.%20I%20don't%20know%20how%20much%20that%20cost%20the%20store%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20food.%20Customers%20would%20come%20in%20and%20ask%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen's%20it%20going%20to%20be%20fixed%3F%26quot%3B%20I%20had%20no%20answer%20because%20all%20we%20could%20do%20was%20put%20in%20a%20service%20ticket.%20The%20first%20time%20it%20happened%2C%20it%20took%20about%20two%20weeks%20before%20someone%20came%20to%20fix%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20long%20after%20we%20opened%2C%20two%20big%20air%20vents%20on%20the%20ceiling%20were%20water%20damaged.%20One%20was%20dripping%20water%2C%20and%20I%20had%20to%20put%20little%20buckets%20to%20catch%20it.%20I%20put%20up%20safety%20signs%2C%20but%20sometimes%20customers%20would%20knock%20them%20over%20with%20their%20carts%20and%20the%20water%20would%20spill%20all%20over%20the%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20were%20the%20restrooms.%20They%20weren't%20heated%2C%20so%20during%20the%20winter%20%E2%80%94%20remember%2C%20the%20store's%20in%20Minnesota%20%E2%80%94%20it%20gets%20a%20wee%20bit%20cold.%20The%20district%20manager%20suggested%20putting%20a%20space%20heater%20in%20each%20restroom.%20There%20was%20no%20outlet%20inside%20either%20one%2C%20so%20we%20were%20told%20to%20run%20extension%20cords.%20That's%20what%20we%20need%2C%20I%20thought%3A%20an%20extension%20cord%20for%20customers%20and%20employees%20to%20trip%20over%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20fire%20hazard%20heaters%20would%20create.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20no%20longer%20work%20there%2C%20but%20I%20went%20to%20the%20store%20the%20other%20day.%20They're%20not%20allowing%20anyone%20to%20use%20the%20bathrooms%20at%20all%20because%20the%20lights%20went%20out%2C%20and%20no%20one%20has%20repaired%20them.%20At%20first%2C%20they%20told%20people%20to%20use%20the%20flashlights%20on%20their%20cellphones.%20Then%20one%20woman%20complained%20that%20she%20had%20bruised%20herself%20in%20the%20dark.%20Now%20the%20bathrooms%20aren't%20open%20to%20the%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20quit%20because%20of%20some%20personal%20things%20but%20also%20because%20the%20management%20and%20the%20problems%20with%20the%20building%20were%20bugging%20the%20crap%20out%20of%20me.%20You're%20telling%20me%20I%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20something%20that's%20not%20my%20fault%2C%20that%20I%20didn't%20cause%20or%20none%20of%20the%20workers%20caused%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20district%20manager%20would%20say%3A%20%26quot%3BOther%20people%20working%20at%20other%20Dollar%20Generals%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20thing%20or%20something%20like%20it.%20They%20have%20problems%20at%20their%20stores%2C%20too.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20not%20really%20the%20employees'%20problem.%20You%20throw%20them%20into%20this%20crappy%20store%20and%20expect%20them%20to%20bring%20in%20profits%2C%20yet%20you%20don't%20fix%20problems%20as%20they%20come%20up.%20And%20you're%20paying%20low%20wages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EA%20Dollar%20General%20spokesperson%20told%20Insider%20that%20it%20works%20with%20third-party%20developer%20partners%20who%20are%20responsible%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20its%20stores%2C%20which%20take%20about%20four%20to%20six%20weeks%20to%20build.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20spokesperson%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BMany%20factors%20can%20result%20in%20a%20new%20construction%20maintenance%20issue.%20Our%20developer%20partners%20and%20teams%20work%20collaboratively%20to%20identify%20and%20then%20correct%20issues%20as%20quickly%20as%20possible.%20When%20a%20maintenance%20issue%20arises%2C%20our%20teams%20work%20to%20assess%20and%20correct%20the%20issue%20as%20soon%20as%20possible%20in%20order%20to%20ensure%20we%20are%20providing%20a%20pleasant%20in-store%20experience%20for%20our%20employees%20and%20customers.%20The%20length%20of%20the%20process%20depends%20on%2C%20among%20other%20things%2C%20the%20specific%20issue%20and%20availability%20of%20parts%20and%20service%20professionals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDo%20you%20work%20at%20a%20Dollar%20General%20store%20and%20have%20a%20story%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20abitter%40insider.com.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworked-new-dollar-general-started-falling-apart-before-it-opened-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699787881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654d4a203cc84b4dfaffbda9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworked-new-dollar-general-started-falling-apart-before-it-opened-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20former%20Dollar%20General%20employee%20recounted%20problems%20at%20a%20new%20store%20in%20Minnesota%2C%20including%20broken%20freezers%2C%20flooding%2C%20and%20dark%20bathrooms.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22abitter%40businessinsider.com%20(Alex%20Bitter)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.busin