awal%20symptoms.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20on%20a%20full%20%26quot%3Bdigital%20detox%26quot%3B%20may%20not%20be%20all%20that%20beneficial%20after%20all%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20study%20by%20researchers%20at%20Durham%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20find%20out%20whether%20%26quot%3Bwithdrawal%20symptoms%26quot%3B%20can%20really%20be%20linked%20to%20social%20media%2C%20they%20asked%2051%20students%20to%20avoid%20sites%20such%20as%20Facebook%2C%20Instagram%2C%20and%20TikTok%20for%20a%20week.%20About%20a%20third%20of%20the%20participants%20had%20social-media%20behaviors%20that%20were%20defined%20as%20problematic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20mood%20was%20tracked%20for%2015%20days%20through%20a%20self-recorded%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20week%2086%25%20%26quot%3Brelapsed%26quot%3B%20at%20least%20once%2C%20but%20their%20average%20use%20time%20remained%20below%2030%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20study%2C%20published%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.plos.org%2Fplosone%2Farticle%3Fid%3D10.1371%2Fjournal.pone.0293467%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPLOS%20ONE%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20found%20that%20there%20was%20no%20evidence%20that%20disconnecting%20from%20your%20online%20life%20produces%20withdrawal%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20say%20that%20the%20findings%20show%20social%20media%20may%20not%20be%20as%20addictive%20as%20some%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fi-took-digital-detox-from-work-stop-checking-my-phone-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edigital%20detox%3C%2Fa%3E%20did%20cause%20the%20participants%20to%20feel%20fewer%20negative%20emotions%2C%20like%20intimidation%20and%20harassment%2C%20and%20many%20reported%20experiencing%20less%20FOMO.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20their%20positive%20interactions%20also%20decreased.%20The%20participants%20experienced%20more%20boredom%20and%20loneliness%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20connectio