rted%20back%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20feasible%26quot%3B%20that%20the%20bishop%20stay%20in%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20revealed%20that%20Strickland%2C%2065%2C%20had%20been%20asked%20on%20Thursday%20to%20resign%2C%20but%20refused%20--%20prompting%20Francis%20to%20step%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Holy%20Father%20has%20relieved%20from%20the%20pastoral%20governance%20of%20the%20diocese%20of%20Tyler%20(US)%20Joseph%20E.%20Strickland%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Vatican%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20the%20bishop%20of%20Austin%2C%20Joe%20Vasquez%2C%20had%20been%20named%20as%20apostolic%20administrator%20of%20the%20diocese%2C%20but%20gave%20no%20further%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20stand%20by%20all%20the%20things%20that%20were%20listed%20as%20complaints%20against%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Strickland%20told%20a%20conservative%20Canadian%20Catholic%20website%20in%20an%20article%20published%20Saturday%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20did%20not%20implement%20some%20of%20Francis's%20reforms%20because%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20starve%20out%20part%20of%20my%20flock.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'd%20do%20it%20the%20same%20way%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20was%20quoted%20by%20LifeSiteNews%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E-%20'Reactionary%20attitude'%20-%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStrickland%20was%20appointed%20by%20Benedict%20XVI%20in%202012%2C%20and%20became%20one%20of%20the%20most%20prominent%20critics%20of%20his%20successor%2C%20Pope%20Francis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Argentine%20pope%2C%2086%2C%20has%20sought%20since%20taking%20office%2010%20years%20ago%20to%20forge%20a%20more%20compassionate%20Church%2C%20open%20to%20different%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20has%20faced%20intense%20opposition%20from%20critics%20--%20particularly%20in%20the%20United%20States%20--%20who%20accuse%20him%20of%20causing%20confusion%20and%20failing%20to%20uphold%20key%20Catholic%20beliefs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20message%20earlier%20this%20year%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20Strickland%20said%20that%20while%20he%20recognised%20Francis%20as%20the%20pope%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20reject%20his%20programme%20of%20undermining%20the%20deposit%20of%20faith%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20Francis'%20critics%20complain%20he%20is%20not%20outspoken%20enough%20on%20abortion%20and%20too%20compassionate%20towards%20homosexuals%20and%20divorcees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrancis%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20lamented%20earlier%20this%20year%20the%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20reactionary%20attitude%26quot%3B%20of%20some%20Catholics%20in%20the%20US%2C%20who%20he%20said%20do%20not%20understand%20the%20%26quot%3Bevolution%20in%20the%20understanding%20of%20matters%20of%20faith%20and%20morals%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E-%20'Speak%20His%20truth'%20-%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Vatican%20has%20not%20commented%20on%20its%20inquiry%20into%20the%20Texas%20diocese%2C%20but%20Strickland%20previously%20said%20that%20two%20US%20bishops%20spent%20a%20week%20conducting%20interviews%20--%20including%20with%20him%20--%20about%20the%20situation%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20blog%20post%20in%20September%2C%20he%20addressed%20rumours%20that%20he%20would%20be%20asked%20to%20leave%20voluntarily.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20cannot%20resign%20as%20bishop%20of%20Tyler%20because%20that%20would%20be%20me%20abandoning%20the%20flock%26quot%3B%20under%20his%20care%2C%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20also%20said%20that%20I%20will%20respect%20the%20authority%20of%20Pope%20Francis%20if%20he%20removes%20me%20from%20office%20as%20Bishop%20of%20Tyler.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20he%20loved%20Jesus%20Christ%20and%20the%20Church%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bmy%20only%20desire%20is%20to%20speak%20His%20truth%20and%20live%20God's%20will%20to%20the%20best%20of%20my%20ability%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECommentators%20say%20it%20is%20extremely%20rare%20for%20a%20bishop%20to%20be%20directly%20relieved%20of%20their%20position%20--%20but%20not%20unprecedented.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrancis%20dismissed%20a%20bishop%20in%20Puerto%20Rico%2C%20Daniel%20Fernandez%20Torres%2C%20in%20similar%20fashion%20in%20March%202022%2C%20with%20the%20Vatican%20again%20giving%20no%20reason.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETorres%20claimed%20he%20had%20been%20told%20he%20had%20not%20been%20%26quot%3Bobedient%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20pope%20and%20did%20not%20have%20sufficiently%20good%20relationships%20with%20fellow%20bishops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMedia%20reports%20at%20the%20time%20noted%20he%20had%20supported%20those%20who%20refused%20compulsory%20coronavirus%20vaccinations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20published%20on%20Saturday%2C%20Cardinal%20DiNardo%2C%20who%20is%20also%20Archbishop%20of%20Galveston-Houston%20in%20Texas%2C%20explained%20the%20process%20with%20Strickland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20visit%20to%20the%20Tyler%20diocese%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20recommendation%20was%20made%20to%20the%20Holy%20Father%20that%20the%20continuation%20in%20office%20of%20Bishop%20Strickland%20was%20not%20feasible%26quot%3B%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20to%20ask%20Strickland%20to%20resign%20--%20and%20ultimately%20dismiss%20him%20--%20followed%20%26quot%3Bmonths%20of%20careful%20consideration%26quot%3B%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20more%20than%20120%2C000%20Catholics%20in%20the%20diocese%20of%20Tyler%2C%20out%20of%20a%20total%20population%20of%20more%20than%201.4%20million%20people%2C%20according%20to%20the%20US%20Conference%20of%20Catholic%20Bishops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(This%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20auto-generated%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699768440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-06%2Fa2gcnf3_pope-francis-afp-_625x300_18_June_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fin-rare-move-pope-sacks-us-bishop