nt%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699709996000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F30C9%2Fproduction%2F_131698421_p0gs4rnp.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-67390345%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Visitors%20have%20been%20flocking%20to%20the%20Kealia%20Pond%20National%20Wildlife%20Refuge%20to%20see%20the%20spectacle.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A531%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fav%2Fworld-us-canada-67390345%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Malayalam%20Film%20'Aattam'%20Shows%20How%20the%20Truth%20Can%20be%20Messy%20and%20Complicated%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F11173301%2FThe-Wire-75.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHow%20many%20more%20lies%20do%20I%20need%20to%20tell%20to%20prove%20to%20everyone%20that%20I%E2%80%99m%20telling%20the%20truth%3F%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20visibly%20shaken%20Anjali%20(Zarin%20Shihab)%20asks%20Vinay%20(Vinay%20Forrt)%20in%20Anand%20Ekarshi%E2%80%99s%20Malayalam%20film%2C%20%3Cem%3EAattam%20(The%20Play)%3C%2Fem%3E.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20loaded%20and%20absolutely%20necessary%20question%20for%20our%20paradoxical%20times%3A%20when%20humility%20is%20bragged%20about%2C%20solitude%20is%20an%20aesthetic%20to%20be%20exhibited%20to%20crowds%20on%20social%20media%2C%20and%20where%20a%20victim%20needs%20to%20be%20perfect%2C%20while%20empathy%20and%20nuance%20are%20lopsided%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20accused.%20The%20truth%20needs%20to%20be%20unblemished%20and%20padded%20with%20just%20the%20right%20amount%20of%20believability.%20Few%20want%20to%20grapple%20with%20the%20messy%2C%20contradictory%20nature%20of%20%3Cem%3Ethe%3C%2Fem%3E%20truth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnjali%20is%20an%20interior%20designer%2C%20who%20has%20been%20pursuing%20her%20love%20for%20acting%20as%20a%20part%20of%20a%20theatre%20group%20for%20over%2016%20years.%20She%E2%80%99s%20the%20only%20girl%20in%20the%20cast.%20Ekarshi%20addresses%20it%20early%20on%20in%20the%20film%20when%20a%20journalist%20poses%20the%20question%20to%20the%20director%20of%20the%20play%20in%20the%20film%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9CWhy%20is%20there%20just%20one%20girl%20in%20the%20cast%3F%E2%80%9D%20Like%20most%20things%20here%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20deliberate%20choice.%20The%20lead%20actor%20in%20the%20play%2C%20Hari%20(Kalabhavan%20Shahjohn)%20%E2%80%93%20depicted%20as%20a%20moderately-famous%20movie%20star%2C%20who%20joined%20the%20group%20two%20years%20ago%20%E2%80%93%20invites%20a%20few%20British%20friends%20to%20their%20performance.%20They%E2%80%99re%20so%20impressed%20by%20the%20play%20that%20they%20offer%20their%20villa%20to%20the%20group%20for%20a%20post-performance%20celebration.%20The%20entire%20group%20meets%20at%20the%20villa%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20evening%20is%20doused%20in%20alcohol%20and%20laughs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEkarshi%2C%20whose%20first%20film%20this%20is%2C%20sets%20up%20the%20interpersonal%20dynamics%20within%20the%20group%20in%20an%20economical%20and%20brisk%20first%2025%20minutes.%20Vinay%20used%20to%20be%20the%20lead%20in%20the%20play%20before%20Hari%20joined%20the%20group%2C%20but%20since%20then%2C%20%5Bbecause%20of%20his%20popularity%5D%2C%20they%E2%80%99ve%20been%20doing%20more%20shows%20and%20more%20people%20are%20turning%20up%20to%20watch.%20Vinay%2C%20who%20is%20waiting%20for%20his%20divorce%20to%20come%20through%2C%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20told%20the%20group%20that%20he%20and%20Anjali%20are%20in%20love.%20Prasanth%20(Prasanth%20Madhavan)%20is%20in%20love%20with%20Anjali%2C%20and%20when%20he%20tries%20to%20express%20it%20to%20her%2C%20she%20rebuffs%20him.%20Sijin%20(Sijin%20Sijeesh)%20has%20a%20bone%20to%20pick%20with%20Anjali%2C%20because%20he%20heard%20she%20played%20a%20role%20in%20calling%20off%20his%20marriage%20to%20Anjali%E2%80%99s%20cousin.%20The%20elders%20in%20the%20group%20think%20of%20Anjali%20as%20her%C2%A0%20%E2%80%98daughter%2Fsister%E2%80%99%2C%20or%20at%20least%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20they%20all%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20morning%20after%20the%20celebration%20at%20the%20villa%2C%20Anjali%20is%20nowhere%20to%20be%20found.%20When%20Vinay%20tries%20to%20call%20her%2C%20she%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20pick%20up.%20A%20few%20days%20later%2C%20Anjali%20meets%20Vinay%20and%20tells%20him%20she%20was%20groped%20that%20night.%20She%20was%20asleep%20near%20a%20window%2C%20when%20she%20felt%20a%20hand%20come%20in.%20She%20managed%20to%20grab%20the%20person%E2%80%99s%20pocket%20and%20car%20keys%20fell%20out.%20She%20suspects%20it%20was%20Hari%20because%20the%20keys%20belong%20to%20him.%20Vinay%20is%20angry%2C%20and%20suggests%20Anjali%20inform%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20group%20so%20he%20can%20be%20expelled.%20Initially%2C%20Anjali%20is%20hesitant.%20But%20Vinay%20convinces%20her%20to%20let%20him%20approach%20Madan%20(Madan%20Babu)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20coordinator%20of%20the%20theatre%20group.%20He%20asks%20Madan%20to%20tell%20everyone%20that%20Anjali%20approached%20him%20with%20the%20complaint%2C%20and%20requests%20him%20to%20call%20the%20entire%20group%20to%20decide%20on%20Hari%E2%80%99s%20fate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20where%20Ekarshi%E2%80%99s%20film%20%E2%80%93%20his%20tribute%20(and%20subversion)%20to%20Sidney%20Lumet%E2%80%99s%20iconic%20chamber%20drama%2C%20%3Cem%3E12%20Angry%20Men%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1957)%20%E2%80%94%20actually%20begins.%20Everyone%20in%20the%20theatre%20group%2C%20barring%20Hari%2C%20reaches%20Madan%E2%80%99s%20house.%20They%E2%80%99re%20informed%20about%20Anjali%E2%80%99s%20allegation%20against%20Hari%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20fascinating%20how%20each%20of%20them%20responds.%20There%E2%80%99s%20initial%20rage%20and%20disgust%20%E2%80%93%20someone%20casually%20says%20how%20he%E2%80%99ll%20lynch%20Hari%20the%20next%20time%20he%20sees%20him.%20Someone%20tries%20to%20ask%20basic%20questions%20%E2%80%93%20%E2%80%9CHow%20does%20she%20know%20it%20was%20Hari%3F%20Did%20she%20see%20him%3F%E2%80%9D%20One%20of%20them%20opines%20how%20the%20scandal%20could%20smear%20the%20name%20of%20the%20theatre%20group%2C%20and%20no%20women%20might%20want%20to%20join%20them%20in%20the%20near%20future.%20Someone%20talks%20about%20a%20compromise%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20reached%20between%20Hari%20and%20Anjali%2C%20while%20another%20one%20of%20them%20simply%20shuts%20down%20any%20talk%20about%20a%20compromise%2C%20stating%20unequivocally%20that%20they%20should%20just%20expel%20Hari%20and%20go%20public%20about%20it%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20only%20responsible%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20discussion%20in%20%3Cem%3EAattam%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20mirrors%20our%20social%20media%20discourse.%20Most%20people%20tend%20to%20come%20from%20a%20place%20of%20pure%20intention%2C%20but%20with%20varying%20degrees%20of%20empathy%2C%20sensitivity%2C%20cultural%20biases%2C%20intellectual%2C%20and%20financial%20limitations.%20Just%20like%20everyone%20on%20social%20media%20is%20brought%20to%20believe%3A%20everyone%20has%20a%20right%20to%20an%20opinion.%20But%20are%20all%20opinions%20equally%20well%20thought-out%3F%20How%20many%20of%20us%20introspect%20when%20our%20core%20beliefs%20are%20challenged%20by%20someone%20more%20articulate%3F%20It%E2%80%99s%20exactly%20what%20happens%20when%20the%20characters%20in%20Ekarshi%E2%80%99s%20film%20%E2%80%93%20all%20coming%20from%20different%20walks%20of%20life%20%E2%80%93%20bring%20together%20an%20entire%20bouquet%20of%20thoughts%2Fopinions.%20Amidst%20all%20this%20talk%2C%20how%20quickly%20does%20the%20main%20point%20of%20contention%20recede%20into%20the%20background%3F%20Is%20anyone%20keeping%20track%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Lumet%E2%80%99s%20classic%20film%2C%20the%20contrarian%20is%20the%20hero.%20All%20jurors%20seem%20to%20be%20in%20a%20rush%20to%20pronounce%20their%20judgements%20and%20do%20away%20with%20the%20accused.%20However%2C%20the%20one%20who%20asks%20everyone%20to%20reconsider%20ultimately%20ends%20up%20swaying%20the%20room.%20In%20Ekarshi%E2%80%99s%20version%2C%20we%20see%20Sijin%20express%20his%20doubts%20in%20Anjali%E2%80%99s%20account.%20Only%20a%20scene%20later%2C%20his%20bias%20against%20Anjali%20%E2%80%93%20for%20breaking%20up%20his%20prospective%20marriage%20with%20her%20cousin%20%E2%80%93%20is%20revealed.%20Selvan%2C%20an%20elder%20in%20the%20group%2C%20calls%20Anjali%20his%20%E2%80%98daughter%E2%80%99%2C%20but%20follows%20it%20up%20with%20how%20she%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20drinking%20recklessly%20or%20dressing%20in%20a%20certain%20way.%20The%20group%20delves%20into%20details%20of%20Anjali%E2%80%99s%20account%2C%20relying%20on%20their%20memory%2C%20and%20tries%20to%20look%20for%20hints%20of%20guilt%20in%20their%20conversations%20with%20Hari%2C%20in%20the%20days%20after%20the%20celebration%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEkarshi%20introduces%20another%20delicious%20plot-point%2C%20where%20the%20group%20stands%20to%20gain%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20money%20with%20their%20continued%20association%20with%20Hari%2C%20making%20even%20the%20most%20cocksure%20theatre%20group%20members%20wobble%20about%20their%20stance%20about%20expelling%20him.%20As%20Anjali%20is%20summoned%20by%20the%20group%2C%20and%20tiny%20inconsistencies%20emerge%20in%20her%20account%2C%20it%20takes%20only%20a%20few%20moments%20for%20all%20these%20%E2%80%9Callies%E2%80%9D%20to%20reconsider%20their%20stance.%20Most%20of%20the%20men%2C%20with%20their%20male-saviour%20complex%2C%20are%20revealed%20to%20be%20squabbling%20infants.%20Some%20are%20blinded%20by%20the%20riches%20they%20stand%20to%20gain%2C%20as%20against%20backing%20an%20imperfect%20victim%20with%20probable%20%E2%80%98holes%E2%80%99%20in%20her%20story.%20While%20the%20others%20are%20simply%20too%20egotistical%20to%20look%20beyond%20their%20biases%20and%20consider%20the%20cold%20facts%20of%20the%20case.%20Beyond%20a%20point%2C%20no%20one%E2%80%99s%20interested%20in%20learning%20what%20really%20happened%2C%20only%20the%20least%20obtrusive%20way%20to%20%E2%80%98move%20on%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAattam%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20the%20kind%20of%20chamber%20drama%20that%20one%20would%20liken%20to%20an%20action%20film%2C%20where%20characters%20fight%20with%20words%20%5Blike%20a%20Sorkin%20film%5D.%20Ideas%20are%20thrown%20at%20each%20other%2C%20and%20while%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20chance%20that%20one%20is%20better%20than%20the%20other%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20more%20fascinating%20when%20both%20characters%20have%20a%20point.%20Real%20life%2C%20after%20all%2C%20is%20full%20of%20ambiguous%20circumstances%20that%20prod%20us%20to%20think%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20would%20I%20have%20done%3F%E2%80%9D%20Barring%20Vijay%20Forrt%2C%20the%20others%20are%20relatively%20unknown%20on%20the%20screen%2C%20which%20is%20a%20good%20thing%2C%20because%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20any%20preconceived%C2%A0notions%20about%20the%20characters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20shown%20recently%20at%20the%20MAMI%20Film%20Festival%20and%20had%20earlier%20won%20an%20award%20at%20the%20Indian%20Film%20Festival%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20will%20eventually%20be%20on%20an%20OTT%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20Indian%20films%20haven%E2%80%99t%20been%20able%20to%20do%20justice%20to%20the%20nuances%20of%20the%20%23MeToo%20movement%2C%20or%20showcase%20the%20messy%20aftermath%20of%20a%20sexual%20harassment%20investigation.%20Ekarshi%E2%80%99s%20film%20seems%20to%20understand%20and%20closely%20observe%20the%20ignorance%20of%20the%20Indian%20man%2C%20who%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20learned%20sensitivity%20and%20is%20largely%20clueless%20about%20asking%20the%20%E2%80%98right%E2%80%99%20questions%20to%20an%20alleged%20victim.%20Amidst%20all%20this%2C%20%3Cem%3EAattam%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20sure%20about%20one%20thing%20though%3A%20most%20Indian%20men%20wanting%20to%20play%20%E2%80%98saviours%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98allies%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20can%E2%80%99t%20handle%20the%20